# Architecture Patterns

## Layers and Responsibilities

### Pages (`src/pages/**`)

- Define route-level structure and composition
- Call `usePageSEO` to set per-page title and description
- Wire together one or more feature containers (hero, gallery, services, prices, reviews, contact)
- Should not contain low-level layout CSS or business logic

### Containers (`src/components/**/Feature.jsx`)

- Own feature-level state, data loading, and side effects
- Compose one or more presentational views
- Call custom hooks from `src/hooks/**`
- Map data and callbacks into view props

### Views (`src/components/**/FeatureView.jsx`)

- Receive all data and callbacks via props
- Render JSX only (no data fetching, no side effects)
- Can be tested in isolation with simple props

### Hooks (`src/hooks/**`)

- Encapsulate reusable logic (data fetching, sliders, responsive behavior, SEO, etc.)
- Never render JSX
- Should be small and focused (one responsibility)

### Data & Translations (`src/data/**`, `src/translations/**`)

- `src/data/**` holds structured data (services, images, slider config)
- `src/translations/**` holds EN/BG translation objects for all UI text and SEO metadata
- React components consume these modules instead of hardcoding strings

## Container / View Pattern

### Example Structure

```
src/components/Services/
  Services.jsx       (container)
  ServicesView.jsx   (view)
  Services.css
```

### Container Example

```jsx
import { useServices } from '../../hooks/useServices'
import { ServicesView } from './ServicesView'

export const Services = ({ showSeeAll }) => {
  const { lang, services, isLoading } = useServices()

  if (isLoading) return null

  return (
    <ServicesView
      lang={lang}
      services={services}
      showSeeAll={showSeeAll}
    />
  )
}
```

### View Example

```jsx
import './Services.css'

export const ServicesView = ({ lang, services, showSeeAll }) => {
  return (
    <section className="services">
      <div className="container">
        <div className="services-grid">
          {services.map(service => (
            <div key={service.id} className="service-card">
              <h3>{service.name[lang]}</h3>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  )
}
```

## When to Split into Container + View

- The component:
  - Uses multiple hooks
  - Handles data fetching or transforms
  - Has several event handlers or side effects
  - Is becoming hard to read or test
- In these cases, move logic to `Feature.jsx` and keep `FeatureView.jsx` purely presentational.

